{
  "doc_id": "18204",
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , the BoF model is used for time-series representation and the dictionary is optimized using a discriminative loss function. In [CITATION_2] , a similar BoF-based approach is combined with a retrieval-oriented loss function to optimize the representation towards retrieval. Also, in [CITATION_3] , time-series segments of various lengths are used during the feature extraction, which allows for handling warping, and the output of a Random Forest classifier is used to alter the codebook. To the best of our knowledge the proposed method is the first that allows for the end-to-end optimization of a Neural BoF model towards time-series classification.",
